dspace-development.title: E-Persons should be encoded with UTF-8

comments.body: This was manually corrected. The high ID # suggests that this researcher logged in through Shibboleth, meaning this error could have occurred anywhere among the many handoffs between dataspace and shibboleth. Thankfully it can be corrected in Dataspace. Putting this in the icebox, since there is a manual solution when necessary. But according to Atmire, there is no straightforward solution.

marc_liberation.title: Update electronic access fields using the full dump

comments.body:
~~The proposal from @kevinreiss and @mzelesky is not to use umlaut on the record page like we currently do. But to query solr on the isbn, issn and oclc and populate the 'Online Section' in the record page relying on the indexed information.~~ (this comment moved to pulibrary/orangelight#2273)

We will index the records from the full dump using the information provided in the the 951 filed (electronic enrichment fields) and the 856.

This is the bug:

* https://github.com/lostisland/faraday/issues/139
* https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/2567

I can observe the records coming in from Faraday as ascii-8bit but I can't get a fixture to work for a test. Rails is too good at preferring utf-8 at every step along the way.
